14: # AI Council State Format
15: 
16: `ai-council-state.jsonl` is append-only JSONL. Each line is one state event used for resume, audit, and convergence decisions.
17: 
18: ---
19: 
20: ## 1. OVERVIEW
21: 
22: Every council run MUST close with a `council_complete` event appended after `writeReport(...)` lands `council-report.md`. Runs that exit before `council_complete` are incomplete and should be resumed or rolled back before completion is claimed.
23: 
24: ```ts
25: type RoundStart = {
26:   event: "round_start";
27:   round: number;
28:   timestamp: string;
29:   seats: string[];
30: };
31: 
32: type SeatReturned = {
33:   event: "seat_returned";
34:   round: number;
35:   seat: string;
36:   timestamp: string;
37:   status: "ok" | "timeout" | "error";
38:   tokens?: number;
39: };
40: 
41: type DeliberationSynthesized = {
42:   event: "deliberation_synthesized";
43:   round: number;
44:   timestamp: string;
45:   convergence_score?: number;
46: };
47: 
48: type RoundEnd = {
49:   event: "round_end";
50:   round: number;
51:   timestamp: string;
52:   new_findings_count?: number;
53: };
54: 
55: type CouncilComplete = {
56:   event: "council_complete";
57:   timestamp: string;
58:   final_report_path: string;
59:   convergence?: boolean;
60: };
61: 
62: type ArtifactWritten = {
63:   event: "artifact_written";
64:   path: string;
65:   bytes: number;
66:   checksum: `sha256:${string}`;
67:   timestamp: string;
68:   seat_id?: string | null;
69:   round_id: `round-${string}`;
70: };
71: 
72: type Rollback = {
73:   event: "rollback";
74:   round_id: `round-${string}`;
75:   reason: string;
76:   timestamp: string;
77:   supersedes?: string[];
78: };
79: 
80: type ArtifactSuperseded = {
81:   event: "artifact_superseded";
82:   original_path: string;
83:   round_id: `round-${string}`;
84:   rollback_event_id: string;
85:   superseded_by: "rollback";
86:   timestamp: string;
87: };
88: ```
89: 
90: ---
91: 
92: ## 2. OPTIONAL METADATA FIELDS
93: 
94: Helper-emitted v1.1 and writer-emitted v1.2 rows add three optional metadata fields before the event payload:
95: 
96: ```ts
97: type StateMetadata = {
98:   schema_version?: "1.1" | "1.2";
99:   protocol?: "ai-council";
100:   producer?: "persist-artifacts.cjs@1.1.0" | "persist-artifacts@1.2.0";
101: };
102: ```
103: 
104: Examples:
105: 
106: - `schema_version: "1.1"` identifies helper-emitted rows; `schema_version: "1.2"` identifies scoped writer rows. Missing means implicit v1.
107: - `protocol: "ai-council"` distinguishes council state from other JSONL logs.
108: - `producer: "persist-artifacts.cjs@1.1.0"` identifies the writer family and version.
109: 
110: Consumers MUST treat these fields as optional. The event `event` value remains the semantic discriminator.
111: 
112: ---
113: 
114: ## 3. SCHEMA EVOLUTION POLICY
115: 
116: State schema evolution is additive-only:
117: 
118: 1. New fields may be added when old readers can ignore them.
119: 2. Missing metadata fields default to v1 semantics.
120: 3. v1 rows without `schema_version`, `protocol`, or `producer` remain valid.
121: 4. Existing rows are append-only history and MUST NOT be rewritten to backfill metadata.
122: 5. Changes that would break v1 callers require a new packet and explicit migration plan.
123: 
124: This follows agent body §14 and ADR-001 in the internal design notes.
125: 
126: ---
127: 
128: ## 4. WORKED EXAMPLE
129: 
130: ```jsonl
131: {"event":"round_start","round":1,"timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:00:00.000Z","seats":["seat-001","seat-002","seat-003"]}
132: {"event":"seat_returned","round":1,"seat":"seat-001","timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:01:00.000Z","status":"ok","tokens":1400}
133: {"event":"seat_returned","round":1,"seat":"seat-002","timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:01:30.000Z","status":"ok","tokens":1320}
134: {"event":"seat_returned","round":1,"seat":"seat-003","timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:02:00.000Z","status":"ok","tokens":1510}
135: {"event":"deliberation_synthesized","round":1,"timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:03:00.000Z","convergence_score":0.84}
136: {"event":"round_end","round":1,"timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:03:30.000Z","new_findings_count":0}
137: {"event":"council_complete","timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:04:00.000Z","final_report_path":"ai-council/council-report.md","convergence":true}
138: ```
139: 
140: ---
141: 
142: ## 5. WORKED EXAMPLE (V1.1)
143: 
144: ```jsonl
145: {"schema_version":"1.1","protocol":"ai-council","producer":"persist-artifacts.cjs@1.1.0","event":"round_start","round":1,"timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:00:00.000Z","seats":["seat-001","seat-002","seat-003"]}
146: {"schema_version":"1.1","protocol":"ai-council","producer":"persist-artifacts.cjs@1.1.0","event":"seat_returned","round":1,"seat":"seat-001","timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:01:00.000Z","status":"ok","tokens":1400}
147: {"schema_version":"1.1","protocol":"ai-council","producer":"persist-artifacts.cjs@1.1.0","event":"seat_returned","round":1,"seat":"seat-002","timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:01:30.000Z","status":"ok","tokens":1320}
148: {"schema_version":"1.1","protocol":"ai-council","producer":"persist-artifacts.cjs@1.1.0","event":"seat_returned","round":1,"seat":"seat-003","timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:02:00.000Z","status":"ok","tokens":1510}
149: {"schema_version":"1.1","protocol":"ai-council","producer":"persist-artifacts.cjs@1.1.0","event":"deliberation_synthesized","round":1,"timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:03:00.000Z","convergence_score":0.84}
150: {"schema_version":"1.1","protocol":"ai-council","producer":"persist-artifacts.cjs@1.1.0","event":"round_end","round":1,"timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:03:30.000Z","new_findings_count":0}
151: {"schema_version":"1.1","protocol":"ai-council","producer":"persist-artifacts.cjs@1.1.0","event":"council_complete","timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:04:00.000Z","final_report_path":"ai-council/council-report.md","convergence":true}
152: ```
153: 
154: ---
155: 
156: ## 5.1 WORKED EXAMPLE (V1.2 AUDIT TRAIL)
157: 
158: v1.2 adds audit events to the same append-only JSONL. Each artifact write records the relative `ai-council/` path, byte count, sha256 checksum, timestamp, optional seat id, and round id.
159: 
160: ```jsonl
161: {"schema_version":"1.2","protocol":"ai-council","producer":"persist-artifacts@1.2.0","event":"artifact_written","path":"ai-council-state.jsonl","bytes":842,"checksum":"sha256:0123456789abcdef0123456789abcdef0123456789abcdef0123456789abcdef","timestamp":"2026-05-08T22:30:00.000Z","seat_id":null,"round_id":"round-001"}
162: {"schema_version":"1.2","protocol":"ai-council","producer":"persist-artifacts@1.2.0","event":"artifact_written","path":"seats/round-001/seat-001-cli-opencode.md","bytes":2048,"checksum":"sha256:aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa","timestamp":"2026-05-08T22:30:01.000Z","seat_id":"seat-001","round_id":"round-001"}
163: {"schema_version":"1.2","protocol":"ai-council","producer":"persist-artifacts@1.2.0","event":"rollback","round_id":"round-001","reason":"seat-002 timed out","timestamp":"2026-05-08T22:31:00.000Z","rollback_event_id":"rollback-round-001-20260508T223100Z","supersedes":["seats/round-001/seat-001-cli-opencode.md"]}
164: {"schema_version":"1.2","protocol":"ai-council","producer":"persist-artifacts@1.2.0","event":"artifact_superseded","original_path":"seats/round-001/seat-001-cli-opencode.md","round_id":"round-001","rollback_event_id":"rollback-round-001-20260508T223100Z","superseded_by":"rollback","timestamp":"2026-05-08T22:31:00.000Z"}
165: ```
166: 
167: v1 readers must ignore `artifact_written`, `rollback`, and `artifact_superseded` events without error. v1.2 readers use them for completeness summaries, checksum verification, and rollback forensics.
168: 
169: ---
170: 
171: ## 6. RESUME SEMANTICS
172: 
173: The last completed event determines the next action. If `round_start` exists without all expected `seat_returned` events, redo or complete that round. If all seats returned but `deliberation_synthesized` is missing, synthesize deliberation. If deliberation exists but `round_end` is missing, close the round. If `council_complete` exists, treat the council as done unless the user requests another round.
174: 
175: ---
176: 
177: ## 7. VALIDATION POLICY
178: 
179: Per ADR-003, validation is convention-only for v1. Do not add a runtime schema validator unless a follow-on packet proves real drift.
